---
title: Beef & Black Bean Chili Includes recyclable aluminum tray
description: You'll combine Tex-Mex seasoned ground beef, tomatoes beef stock, and black beans right in our oven-ready tray to make a delicious, saucy, and super easy-to-assemble chili. Serve it with a sprinkle of melty Monterey Jack, a dollop of sour cream, and a dash of hot sauce. But the best part? Toss the tray when you're done for practically no cleanup!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/673b9bb2fd3e9058428acbf2-f8511f3c.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/673b9bb2fd3e9058428acbf2-en-US.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/prep-and-bake-beef-and-black-bean-chili-673b9bb2fd3e9058428acbf2
servings: 2
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 780 kcal
  fat: 40 g
  saturated fat: 15 g
  carbohydrates: 53 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 10 g
  sodium: 1660 mg
cuisine: North America
time required: 40 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Add @ground beef{10%ounce} to #oven-ready aluminum tray{1} and gently break up
into small pieces with a #fork{}. Season with @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon},
@Mexican Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, @salt{1%tsp}, and @pepper{}. (For 4 servings,
divide everything evenly between two trays, using 1 tsp salt for each tray.)

To #tray{} with beef, stir in @beef stock concentrate{1}, @tomato paste{1%unit},
@crushed tomatoes{1%unit}, and @black beans{1} and their liquid. (For 4 servings,
divide everything evenly between both trays.)

Bake on top rack, uncovered, until beef is saucy and cooked through, ~{30-35%minutes}.
> TIP: Place tray on a foil-lined #baking sheet{} to catch any drips!

Once chili is done, taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Divide chili between bowls; top with @Monterey Jack Cheese{1/4%cup}, 
@sour cream{1.5%tablespoon}, and as much @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.

> The best part? Toss the tray when you're done for practically no cleanup!